%N A397703 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k)^4 + omega(k)^4.
%e A397703 964596 is a term since sigma(964596) = 2324224 = 1992192 + 24^4 + 4^4 = psi(964596) + tau(964596)^4 + omega(964596)^4.
%o A397703 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f)^4 + omega(f)^4; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 05 2026
